    "id": "japanese-vegan-sukiyaki-hot-pot",
    "title": "Sukiyaki Hot Pot (虐待のない · Gyakutai no nai)",
    "source": "Veggie Anh",
    "rawTitle": "### Vegan Sukiyaki Hot Pot (**SHOWSTOPPER**)",
    "rawBody": "- **URL:** https://veggieanh.com/vegan-sukiyaki/ ✓ VERIFIED *(Veggie Anh — one-pot Japanese sukiyaki with firm tofu + a multi-mushroom stack (shiitake, king oyster, enoki) + bok choy + carrot in classic warishita-style sweet-savory broth (4 tbsp soy + 2 tbsp mirin + 2 tbsp sugar + 2 cups veg broth). 4 servings, 25 min total. The pan-fry-the-king-oyster-first step is a small but excellent technique for getting Maillard depth into the dish. **Recommended swap for upscale showstopper presentation: thinly-sliced Chunk Steakhouse Cut** (partial-freeze and slice on a deli slicer, shabu-shabu-thin) added at the table just before service so it cooks in the warishita and stays tender. The mushroom stack remains essential for umami — the protein is additive, not a replacement.)*\n\n  **Recipe** (4 servings, per Anh): 2 tbsp cooking oil, 1 onion (sliced), 300 g firm tofu (cubed), 5 shiitake (de-stemmed, scored), 3 king oyster mushrooms (sliced), 100 g enoki (separated), 1 cup chopped bok choy, ½ carrot (sliced thin). **Warishita:** 4 tbsp soy + 2 tbsp mirin + 2 tbsp sugar + 2 cups veg broth. Heat oil over medium; pan-fry king oysters until golden both sides, remove. Add warishita to pot, simmer low. Add onion + carrot + remaining mushrooms + bok choy + tofu. Simmer 5 min until flavors meld. Serve over cooked udon or shirataki noodles, ladling broth over.\n- **Description:** **Lead protein:** Chunk Foods 4-oz Classic Steak partially frozen and shaved on a deli slicer to translucent ribbons (impossible without partial freeze) — the whole-muscle structure means it slices like real wagyu. Cooked tableside in a cast-iron donabe with warishita (mirin-soy-sake-sugar) over yuba (tofu skin), enoki, shiitake, napa cabbage, shungiku, shirataki, and grilled tofu. Diners dip cooked ribbons in a \"raw egg\" substitute (silken tofu + black salt + Kala Namak whipped). The Japanese steakhouse experience, plant-based.\n- **Wholesale food cost:** $5.50 / serving · **Menu price:** **$24–32** (per-person, served family-style for 2)\n- **Weight:** 520 g · **Calories:** 580 · **Protein:** 32 g · **Time:** 30 min (warishita prep + slicing during prep, 8 min cook tableside) · **Servings:** 2 (per donabe)\n- **Restaurant difficulty:** **Hard** — tableside service, deli-slicer-thin protein, the \"egg\" dip is a brand opportunity to talk about Kala Namak. Requires a server-cooks-or-explains protocol.\n- **Tags:** (neither — table-side experience)\n\n| Sub | Effect | Cost delta |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Lead protein:** Chunk 4-oz Steak shaved (default) | Closest to shaved wagyu visual | baseline |\n| Chunk Steakhouse Cut 6 oz shaved | More volume per portion | +$2.20 → menu $28–34 |\n| Beyond Steak Tips, partially frozen and sliced thin | Casual-tier sukiyaki | −$2.00 → menu $19–24 |\n| Premium upgrade: add Juicy Marbles Loin shaved alongside | Two-protein donabe (\"ozeki\" set) | +$5.50 → menu $32–38 |",
