    "id": "japanese-vegan-matcha-cheesecake",
    "title": "Matcha Cheesecake (虐待のない · Gyakutai no nai)",
    "source": "Addicted to Dates",
    "rawTitle": "### Vegan Matcha Cheesecake (**DESSERT**)",
    "rawBody": "- **URL:** https://addictedtodates.com/pistachio-matcha-tart/ ✓ VERIFIED *(Christina Leopold / Addicted to Dates — a no-bake, no-gelling-agent matcha cheesecake titled \"Matcha Cheesecake (No Bake, Vegan)\" despite the URL slug. 4.98/35 votes, 12 servings, 5h45min total. Cookie-base + creamy filling of soaked cashews + soaked pistachios + Violife vegan cream cheese + Greek-style vegan yogurt + maple syrup + cacao butter (the cacao butter is the setting agent — sets in the fridge with no agar/gelatin needed) + matcha + lime. Hints of pistachio, white chocolate, vanilla. Reads as upscale Japanese-pâtisserie crossover.)*\n\n  **Recipe** (12 servings, per Christina Leopold): **Crust** — 160 g vegan digestives or ginger nuts, ½ tsp salt, 60 g vegan butter. Blitz cookies + salt 30 sec; add butter, blend until it sticks; press into a 7\" or 8\" parchment-lined springform; chill. **Filling** — 130 g cashews (soaked 4 hr), 70 g unsalted pistachios (soaked, skins rubbed off), 300 g vegan cream cheese (Violife), 150 g vegan Greek-style yogurt, 150 ml maple syrup, 50 g cacao butter (don't sub coconut oil — cacao butter is the setting agent), 2 tbsp matcha (more to taste), 1 tbsp vanilla bean paste, 1 tbsp lime juice. Blitz all filling ingredients in a high-speed blender until smooth and lump-free; pour into chilled crust; refrigerate 5 hr minimum (or overnight). Garnish with vegan-white-chocolate-matcha shards. Hot wet knife between slices for clean cuts.\n- **Description:** No-bake cookie-crust cheesecake with a creamy cashew-pistachio-Violife filling, set with cacao butter rather than agar (no jelly texture — this is a true creamy cheesecake set). Hints of pistachio + lime + vanilla complement the matcha. Plates beautifully with a single hojicha caramel dot, fresh raspberry, or matcha-white-chocolate shard.\n- **Wholesale food cost:** $2.40 / serving · **Menu price:** $9–14 / $11–14 with hojicha caramel\n- **Weight:** 110 g · **Calories:** 356 · **Protein:** 8 g · **Time:** 45 min active + 5 hr chill · **Servings:** 12 / 7\"–8\" springform\n- **Restaurant difficulty:** **Easy** — no-bake; build whole, slice cold (hot-wet-knife technique), plate with one accent. Holds 5 days refrigerated, 2+ months frozen (slice first, defrost individual portions).\n- **Tags:** 🥘 Bulk-Prep · ⚡ Fast-Service\n\n| Sub | Effect | Cost delta |\n|---|---|---|\n| Default cashew-pistachio Violife filling | Christina's recipe as written; balanced matcha + nutty | baseline ($2.40) |\n| Skip pistachios, swap in equal cashews | Cleaner matcha-forward flavor; ~$0.40 cheaper | −$0.40 |\n| Sunflower-seed nut-free version | Top-9 allergen friendly | flat |\n| Yuzu glaze on top | Citrus brightness, premium read | +$0.30 |\n| Add anko (red bean paste) quenelle | Japanese-pâtisserie premium presentation | +$0.40 → menu $11–14 |\n| Mini portions in muffin pan w/ parchment slings | Tasting-menu format | flat |",
